description:
Transplantation Science is a free program for 7th through 12th graders meant to enhance any anatomy, health or biology program and to introduce students to the world of organ, eye and tissue donation and transplantation.  Through this interactive program students have the chance to:

•	Learn about each transplantable organ and how it functions;
•	Examine real, plastinated organ and tissue specimens from the human body;
•	Learn about the conditions leading to the need for a transplant;
•	Learn how organ allocation works and complete exercises to match example donors and recipients

